\par\pard\plain \sl480\slmult1\qc\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 #}{\*\bkmkstart Character_Generation}
\par\pard\plain \fi720\sl480\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\*\bkmkstart Character_Generation}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The basics of character generation is done using the fate deck, the rules are designed so that you can play any kind of campaign that you want, whether it be a party that is a mix of races, a single race, a single class or an evil campaign. }{\*\bkmkend Character_Generation}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Every decision you have to make along the way is done using the fate deck, there are a number of optional choices towards the end, but first each character begins with 3 fate points, which they can increase or decrease along the way during character building, depending on your race, class and your alignment, some classes and races get extra fate points, and depending on your alignment, if your character is of the light the red joker is your top card and black joker your bottom card, every time you draw your top card you add a fate point and every time you pull your bottom card you lose a fate point, you can never start with less than 2 fate points and never more than 6 fate points, and a character can never end up with more than 10 total fate points.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The next choice you have to do is decide your race, the first entry in the lists is the base stats for that race, each race has a series of strengths and weaknesses, in the case of a human, while they start with a bonus fate point, an extra talent and 4 extra skill points, they have no bonus weapon talents, their stats are baseline. Once you decide your race you draw a card, either note it down or take down the details and move to the next part of character building.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 After you choose your race, next you choose your class, each of the classes from Warrior, to Mage to Paladin to Psionic Warrior, have choices in what kind of that class they are, whether they are the warrior martial artist, the heavy infantryman or the combat specialist, each have their bonus talents, skills, and defense and attack bonuses, as with the racial choice you draw a card, note it down and take the details.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Next you determine your skill points, each class has it's own table, also not every class will have access to a particular skill, for instance warriors don't have access to arcane magic but a mage won't have access to divine magic either, at start no skill can have over 4 points put into it, when determining the number of skill points you have draw a card and note it down and take the details.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 After Skills you determine the talents your character will begin with, these are the abilities your character has that aren't tied to your skills, your race or your class directly , each race and class have bonus talents that they receive but each class also receives a number of talents that will increase either their skills in certain situations, allow them to do more actions of a type, give them extra dice among a number of other things, to do this you draw a card, note it down or take the details.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 If you are a non-magical or psionic class you can skip the next couple of steps, firstly spell/psionic points, so this is the amount of points you can put into buying and increasing your character's ability to use those spells, unless stated in your character build and you have a specific spell list, you draw a card note it down or take details.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Next the number of spells/powers you can cast in any given day without resting, every type of magic user or psionic character has this whether they are an arcanist, a templar or a Telekineticist they will have a strength which varies determined by drawing a card, you can note this down or take the details.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This is the end of the mandatory character building sections of character generation, but there are a number of optional character generation sections, which are choosing a random race, random class, your character's background, character traits (an optional part of character building that is up to your GM whether or not it will be used), character flaws (an optional part of character building that is up to your GM whether or not it will be used).}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 We will now run through a character build, so Fiona wants to build a human war mage with an elemental focus character who is a character of the light, first this means her character starts with a base 4 fate points, an extra talent and 4 extra skill points, so she takes her fate deck and draws a Jack of Diamonds for her race card, she then shuffles the card back in and draws the Red Joker (Huzzah) for her class card, next she draws a 5 of clubs for her skill card, a Black Joker (Ouch) for her Talent card, 9 of Diamonds for her spell points and finally the King of Clubs for the number of spells she can use in a day.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 So let's get it going:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \line So first we figure out her ability scores, which because of the Jack of Diamonds and the Red Joker are pretty good, with strength and constitution as high as they can ben for a starting human character.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Strength     (}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 4+4) =8}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Agility\tab    (3+4)=7}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Will\tab    (3+3)=6}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Intelligence  (3+4)=7}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Co-ordination (3+3)=6}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Charisma\tab    (3+3)=6}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Consciousness (3+3)=6}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Constitution  (4+4)=8}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Next we look at the skills card which was the 5 of clubs meaning that she gets 17 points to put into her skills but because she is human she get's an extra 4 meaning 21 total points, there are a few skills that are already part of the War Mage's arsenal. These skill points plus your ability is the total for your skill rolls}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Close Combat \tab    1+3+7 = 11}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Arcane Magic \tab    1+3+7 = 11}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 acrobatics    \tab    1+2+7 = 10}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Resistance   \tab    1+2+8 = 10}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Command     \tab    2+6   = 8}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Perception    \tab    2+6   = 8}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Education (arcana)       2+7   = 9}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Education (dungeoneering)2+7   = 9}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Survival\tab \tab    2+6   = 8}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Observation\tab    2+6   = 8}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The next step is the talents your character has, War Mages always start with armour training and a single armour focus, and 3 weapon talents and a focus in each of those talents, and two spell talents of your choice, Fiona decides that she want to wield a longsword, an axe and a knife, Medium bladed weapons with longsword focus, Light bladed weapons with Knife focus, and heavy hacking weapons and a great axe focus, and her armour focus will be scale mail armour, and because this is a medium armour she takes armoured spell casting as one of her spell talents, and because she wants her character to be an elemental spell focused character she takes elemental strength which gives her a 2nd dice when casting elemental spells. This leaves her talent for being human and the two talents she got for her card draw, with these she chooses hardy giving her +2 wounds, elemental damage which gives her a 2nd damage dice when using elemental spells, and dodge which gives her character an extra defense dice when defending against ballistic attack.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The next step in character creation because this character is a magic user, so since she drew a 9 of diamonds, her character get 17 points to spend on spells. Each spell is treated as a skill is for points, but the number is the number of dice the player may roll to pass their arcane magic test, this is the only way to }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Elemental Weapon (Medium) 2}
