\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  . using the fate deck to pass a failed check of the dice, a skill check requires the player to choose a colour or suit depending on the difficulty of the test, easy and intermediate colour can be chosen, if the High king (red joker) is pulled it is a pass no matter the difficulty and their fate point is refunded, if the Lord of the Tyranny (black joker) is pulled a further fate point is lost and it fails. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 If it is an opposed check the GM and player both draw a card the Highest card wins, if it is a draw heart, club, diamond, spade is the order of precedence, in the event the player or GM pulls the high king it scores a critical pass and the fate point is refunded, if the GM or player pulls the Lord of Tyranny it causes a critical fail and a 2nd fate point is lost,}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Should the player be an dark character then the Lord of Tyranny replaces the high king and vice versa. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 In the case of a neutral character before play begins in a session the player choose to favour light or dark in that session. }
