\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Traits notes and stuff:}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 All firearms require a simple ballistic test to load powder. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 There are 2 main forms of firearms action available match lock and wheel lock.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Match lock weapons use a slow burning match as their ignition source. They are vulnerable to moisture and impossible to fire if wet.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Having an open flame mounted on the weapon is dangerous.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Match lock weapons extend their critical failure band by 2.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A critical failure while loading powder into a match lock firearm causes the powder to ignite causing d3 burning damage. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Wheel lock weapons are more complex but also safer and more convenient to use. While loaded but not cocked they are reasonably safe from moisture and not prone to accidental discharge. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Wheel lock weapons extend their critical failure band by 1.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Multi barrel (pepperbox):}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 These weapons have a single lock with multiple barrels mounted such that they can be rotated into alignment with the lock to be fired.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 They are nose heavy but each barrel can be fired separately before it is necessary to reload.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Each barrel must be loaded separately once it has been shot.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 It is possible to reload a barrel with other barrels still loaded.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Pepperbox firearms extend their critical failure band by 2, causing all loaded barrels to chain fire; if the shot hit, roll to hit against the original target for each barrel separately  (further critical pass/fail have no effect).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Once this is resolved the firer must roll for recoil injury. This is an automatic hit to the firer's dominant arm with the damage of the weapon plus the number of barrels fired minus the character's strength. Recoil damage is bludgeoning.}
